item.description:
So every once in a while you would like to sync all the git repositories you work/worked on in the past. It cumbersome to always just go trough one by one.
I use this nifty little script:
#!/bin/bash #Define the color yellow for later use YELLOW='\033[0;33m' #Define text reset NC='\033[0m' pathToRepos=~/work/repos for i in `ls $pathToRepos`;do repo=$pathToRepos&quot;/&quot;$i #Get curreny branch name branch=`git -C $repo symbolic-ref --short -q HEAD` if [ -d $repo/.
